      "id": "E2-12-Q1",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "easy",
      "questionText": "Find $\\dfrac{dy}{dx}$ for each of the following.\n\n(a) $y = 5x^3 - 4x^2 + 7x - 2$\n(b) $y = \\dfrac{x^3}{3} - \\dfrac{1}{x^2}$",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) $15x^2-8x+7$, (b) $x^2+\\dfrac{2}{x^3}$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(a) $15x^2$ term correct" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(a) $-8x+7$ terms correct; constant vanishes" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "(b) $\\frac{1}{x^2} = x^{-2}$ rewritten; $\\frac{d}{dx}(x^{-2}) = -2x^{-3}$" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "(b) $x^2+2x^{-3}$ or $x^2+\\frac{2}{x^3}$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $\\frac{d}{dx}(5x^3)=15x^2$; $\\frac{d}{dx}(-4x^2)=-8x$; $\\frac{d}{dx}(7x)=7$; constant $\\to0$",
        "$\\frac{dy}{dx} = 15x^2-8x+7$",
        "(b) $y=\\frac{x^3}{3}-x^{-2}$",
        "$\\frac{dy}{dx}=\\frac{3x^2}{3}-(-2)x^{-3}=x^2+2x^{-3}=x^2+\\frac{2}{x^3}$"
      ],
      "explanation": "Use the power rule: $\\frac{d}{dx}(x^n) = nx^{n-1}$; rewrite negative powers first."
    },
    {
      "id": "E2-12-Q2",
      "type": "short-answer",
      "totalMarks": 4,
      "commandWord": "find",
      "difficulty": "medium",
      "questionText": "The curve $y = 2x^2 - 7x + 3$ has a tangent at the point where $x = 2$.\n\n(a) Find $\\dfrac{dy}{dx}$.\n(b) Find the gradient of the tangent at $x = 2$.\n(c) Find the equation of the tangent at $x = 2$.",
      "answerType": "expression",
      "correctAnswer": "(a) $4x-7$, (b) $1$, (c) $y = x - 5$",
      "tolerance": null,
      "unit": null,
      "markScheme": [
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(a) $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 4x-7$" },
        { "mark": "B1", "desc": "(b) Gradient $= 4(2)-7 = 1$" },
        { "mark": "M1", "desc": "(c) $y$-coordinate: $2(4)-14+3=-3$; tangent through $(2,-3)$ with gradient 1" },
        { "mark": "A1", "desc": "(c) $y = x-5$ cao" }
      ],
      "workingSteps": [
        "(a) $\\frac{dy}{dx} = 4x-7$",
        "(b) At $x=2$: gradient $= 4(2)-7 = 1$",
        "(c) $y$-coordinate at $x=2$: $y=2(4)-7(2)+3=8-14+3=-3$",
        "Tangent: $y-(-3)=1(x-2) \\Rightarrow y=x-5$",
        "Check: at $x=2$: $y=2-5=-3$ ✓"
      ],
      "explanation": "Differentiate to find the gradient function, evaluate at the given $x$, then use point-gradient form."
    },
