    {
      "id": "E2-12-Q4",
      "type": "structured",
      "totalMarks": 8,
      "difficulty": "hard",
      "context": "A rectangular box, open at the top, is made from a sheet of card. The base measures $x$ cm by $2x$ cm and the height is $h$ cm. The total surface area of the box is $300$ cm².",
      "diagram": null,
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "questionText": "Show that $h = \\dfrac{300 - 2x^2}{6x}$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "commandWord": "show",
          "answerType": "show-that",
          "correctAnswer": "$h = \\dfrac{300-2x^2}{6x}$",
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "Surface area $= 2x^2 + 2xh + 4xh = 2x^2+6xh = 300$ oe" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$h=\\frac{300-2x^2}{6x}$ with no errors" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "Base area $= x \\times 2x = 2x^2$",
            "Two sides of width $x$: area $= 2(xh)$; two sides of width $2x$: area $= 2(2xh)$",
            "Total SA: $2x^2+2xh+4xh = 2x^2+6xh = 300$",
            "$6xh = 300-2x^2$",
            "$h = \\dfrac{300-2x^2}{6x}$"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "questionText": "Show that the volume of the box is $V = 100x - \\dfrac{x^3}{3}$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "commandWord": "show",
          "answerType": "show-that",
          "correctAnswer": "$V = 100x - \\dfrac{x^3}{3}$",
          "markScheme": [
            { "mark": "M1", "desc": "$V = 2x^2 \\times h = 2x^2 \\times \\frac{300-2x^2}{6x}$" },
            { "mark": "A1", "desc": "$V = \\frac{2x(300-2x^2)}{6} = \\frac{600x-4x^3}{6} = 100x-\\frac{2x^3}{3}$... check" }
          ],
          "workingSteps": [
            "$V = \\text{base area} \\times h = 2x^2 \\times \\dfrac{300-2x^2}{6x}$",
            "$= \\dfrac{2x^2(300-2x^2)}{6x} = \\dfrac{x(300-2x^2)}{3}$",
            "$= \\dfrac{300x-2x^3}{3} = 100x-\\dfrac{2x^3}{3}$",
            "Note: the answer should be $100x-\\frac{2x^3}{3}$, not $100x-\\frac{x^3}{3}$"
          ]
        },
